{"lemma":"مَنْبَتَيْ","slug":"مَنْبَتَيْ","root":"ن.ب.ت","root_slug":"ن-ب-ت","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-ب-ت","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n1702","n39163","n39164"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8E%D9%86%D9%92%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%AA%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"source, fountainhead, matrix, nidus"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"active participle of نَبَتَ (nabata)","tags":["active","form-of","participle"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"fertile"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Noun of place from the verb نَبَتَ (nabata).\n\nDerived from the active participle of نَبَتَ (nabata)."},"ipa":["/man.bat/","/mun.bit/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n1702","headword_ar":"مُنْبَتٌّ","root":"bt","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unable to proceed in his journey, his camel that bore him having broken down, or stopped from fatigue, or perished;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, * TA;) syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"munoqaTaEN bihi","text_ar":"مُنْقَطَعٌ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Mgh, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who remains on his road unable to attain the place to which he is directing his course, the beast"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camel that bore him"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zahoruhu","text_ar":"ظَهْرُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having broken down, or stopped from fatigue, or perished."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n39163","headword_ar":"مَنْبَتٌ","root":"nbt","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manobitN","text_ar":"مَنْبِتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n39164","headword_ar":"مَنْبِتٌ","root":"nbt","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Origin, or race,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[from which a man springs;] syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSolN","text_ar":"اَصْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L.) So in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu lafiY","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَفِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manobiti SidoqK","text_ar":"مَنْبِتِ صِدْقٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he belongs to an excellent race; is of an excellent origin"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and so in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY A^akorami","text_ar":"فِى اَكْرَمِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmanaAbiti","text_ar":"المَنَابِتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the most generous of origins,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"races."},{"kind":"text","text":"] (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manobitN","text_ar":"مَنْبِتٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place in which plants,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbs, grow:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) dev. from the constant course of speech: analogically it should be ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manobatN","text_ar":"مَنْبَتٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) as the aor. of the verb from which it is derived is not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yanobitu","text_ar":"يَنْبِتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesreh: but there are other examples like it; as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masjidN","text_ar":"مَسجِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maToliEN","text_ar":"مَطْلِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manobatN","text_ar":"مَنْبَتٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", however, also sometimes occurs. (TA.) [Pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manaAbitu","text_ar":"مَنَابِتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["S","K"]}]}}